    mechanismJa: `消化管は口→食道→胃→小腸（十二指腸・空腸・回腸）→大腸→直腸→肛門の一本の管。腸管神経系（ENS）は約5億個のニューロンを持ち脊髄と同等の複雑さで機能する。蠕動運動は自律神経と腸管ニューロンが協調して消化物を推し進める。腸内細菌はビタミンK・短鎖脂肪酸（SCFA）を産生し腸上皮の保護・免疫調節に必須。迷走神経は腸の状態（微生物信号含む）をリアルタイムで脳に伝達する。`,
    mechanismEn: `The gastrointestinal tract is a single tube from mouth → esophagus → stomach → small intestine (duodenum, jejunum, ileum) → large intestine → rectum → anus. The enteric nervous system (ENS) has ~500 million neurons — as complex as the spinal cord. Peristalsis is coordinated by autonomic nerves and enteric neurons. Gut bacteria produce vitamin K and short-chain fatty acids (SCFA) essential for intestinal protection and immune regulation. The vagus nerve transmits real-time gut status (including microbial signals) to the brain.`,
    yogaJa: `①蠕動促進：ねじりポーズ（マリーチャーサナ等）は腸管を物理的に圧迫・解放し蠕動を機械的に補助。②迷走神経-腸軸改善：深い腹式呼吸が迷走神経を活性化→消化機能向上→ガスや膨満感の解消。③コルチゾール低減：慢性ストレスはIBS（過敏性腸症候群）を悪化させる。ヨガのストレス低減がIBSを改善（Kuttner et al., 2006）。④腸内細菌多様性：Madan et al. (2020) でヨガ実践者の腸内フローラ多様性が高く有益菌（ラクトバチルス等）が増加。⑤腸管リンパ刺激：前屈ポーズで腸間膜リンパを活性化し免疫物質の循環を促進。`,
    yogaEn: `① Peristalsis: twisting poses (Marichyasana etc.) physically compress and release the gut, mechanically assisting peristalsis. ② Vagal-gut axis: deep abdominal breathing activates the vagus → improved digestion → gas and bloating relief. ③ Cortisol reduction: chronic stress worsens IBS. Yoga's stress reduction improves IBS (Kuttner et al., 2006). ④ Microbiome diversity: Madan et al. (2020) found yoga practitioners had greater gut microbiome diversity and increased beneficial bacteria (Lactobacillus etc.). ⑤ Mesenteric lymph: forward folds activate mesenteric lymph and circulate immune compounds.`,
